The paper proposes a novel method for semi-supervised learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning. The method involves using Q-learning, which is a reinforcement learning technique, to select high-quality unlabeled samples for co-training. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.CL (Computation and Language)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision)
